<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" font>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Crop Recommendation</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:ital,wght@0,100;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,700;0,900;1,100;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,700;1,900&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />

    <style>
      :root {
        --bg-color-nav: #ffffff;
        --bg-color-form: #ffffff;
        --bg-color-btn1: #62be1f;
        --bg-color-btn2: #6df10f;
        --bg-color: #d1e391;
        --text-color-body: #333;
        --text-color-nav: #62be1f; 
        --text-color-btn: #62be1f;
        --text-color-btn-hover: #effad6;
      }

      html {
        font-size: 16px;
        font-family: "Roboto", sans-serif;
        font-weight: 400;
        font-style: normal;
      }

      * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        text-decoration: none;
        list-style: none;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif; /* Replace with your preferred font */
        outline: none;
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
        font: inherit;
        color: inherit;
      }
      a {
        color: inherit; /* Inherit color from parent */
        text-decoration: none; /* Remove underline */
      }
      body {
        background-color: var(--bg-color);
      }
      .navbar {
        background-color: var(--bg-color-nav);
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
        color: var(--text-color-nav);
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        position: fixed;
        top: 0;
        width: 100%;
        z-index: 5;
        box-shadow: 0px 0.125rem 0.313rem rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      }

      .navbar .logo {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      .navbar ul {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
      }

      .navbar ul li {
        list-style: none;
      }

      .navbar ul li a {
        color: var(--text-color-nav);
        font-size: 1rem;
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
        border-radius: 0.313rem;
        transition: all 0.3s ease;
      }

      .navbar ul li a:hover {
        background-color: var(--bg-color-btn1);
        color: white;
      }
      .container {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 2fr 1fr;
        height: 100%;
      }
      aside {
        background-color: none;
      }
      section {
        color: var(--text-color-body);
        border-radius: 4px;
        border: 0.0125rem solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        padding: 2rem;
        background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);
        box-shadow: 0px 0.2rem 0.5rem rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        height: 35rem;
      }
      p {
        line-height: 1.4rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="navbar">
      <div class="logo">
        <a href="#">Next generation agriculture</a>
      </div>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="container">
      <aside></aside>
      <section>
        <h3
          style="font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 0.75rem"
        >
          Recommended Crops Based on Soil & Environmental Factors:
        </h3>
        <p>
          Based on the soil and environmental parameters you've provided, <b style="font-weight: 700;"><%= crop %></b>
          is a highly suitable crop to grow in these conditions. With optimal
          nitrogen (N), phosphorus (P), and potassium (K) levels, and a growing
          period of approximately <%=growing_period %> days, Rice is likely to yield
          well. Ensure adequate irrigation as per the recommended moisture
          levels.
        </p>
        <p style="text-indent: 3rem">
          Alternatively, you could also consider crops like Wheat, Maize, or
          Soybeans, which could perform reasonably well with minor adjustments
          to moisture or pH conditions. These options provide flexibility based
          on market demands or resource availability.
        </p>
        <br><br><hr>
      </section>
      <aside></aside>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
